Material Information Summary (ASX:KAI – 6 August 2025 Announcement)

Key Highlights:

  • New gold discovery: Drilling intercepted a significant new zone ("Monster") near Main Hill at Mt York, WA:
  • Best intercept: 53m @ 1.45 g/t Au (incl. 10m @ 2.95 g/t Au).
  • Mineralisation remains open in all directions, with potential to expand the 1.4Moz resource.
  • Drilling progress:
  • 52 holes completed (13,536m) in Stage 1 (80-hole, 18,000m program).
  • Results from 19 holes reported, including high-grade intercepts:
    • 3m @ 7.20 g/t Au (Gossan Hill).
    • 62m @ 0.78 g/t Au (Main Hill).
  • Resource impact: Results expected to boost resource size ahead of an updated MRE in 2H 2025.
  • Next steps:
  • Additional drilling to test extensions of the "Monster" zone.
  • Finalise mineral rights agreement with PLS for further exploration.
  • Commence Pre-Feasibility Study (PFS) work, including metallurgical testing.

Valuation Impact:

  • Potential resource upgrade from new high-grade intercepts and extensional drilling.
  • Progress toward development studies (PFS, metallurgy) supports project de-risking.

Material Information Summary: ACCENT Trial Topline Data (6 August 2025)

Key Clinical Trial Results

  • Progression-Free Survival (PFS): 7.6 months (vs. 5.5 months for standard chemotherapy in MPACT study).
  • Durability: Mean Days on Trial (DOT) of 202 days (vs. 117 days for chemotherapy).
  • Response Rates:
  • Objective Response Rate (ORR): 31% (vs. 23% for chemotherapy).
  • Disease Control Rate (DCR): 73% (vs. 50% for chemotherapy).
  • Includes 1 confirmed Complete Response (CR) and 1 pathological Complete Response (pCR).
  • Tolerability: Safety profile similar to chemotherapy alone, with no significant additional adverse events.

Upcoming Catalysts

  • Further ACCENT trial updates expected in 2H 2025.
  • Mature data (including Overall Survival) expected in Q1 2026.
  • Planned pivotal Phase 2b/3 trial initiation in 2H 2026.

Regulatory & Pipeline Developments

  • FDA Fast Track and Orphan Drug Designation granted.
  • US Phase 1b/2a "AMPLICITY" trial (narmafotinib + FOLFIRINOX) to begin imminently.

Investment Implications

  • Positive interim data supports potential superiority over standard chemotherapy in pancreatic cancer.
  • Upcoming milestones (FDA engagement, pivotal trial planning) key for valuation re-rating.

No material capital structure or financing updates identified.

Key Highlights (GLE/SILEX Uranium Enrichment Technology)

  • TRL-6 Pilot Testing Progress:
  • Large-scale enrichment testing ongoing at GLE’s Wilmington facility; positive results observed, but optimization continues.

  • Independent validation report expected by end of CY2025.

  • Paducah Land Acquisition:

  • DOE Funding & Government Support:

  • Awarded US$0.5M under LEU RFP Task Order 1 (total program: US$3.4B).
  • Up to US$900M available in Task Order 2 (bid due 25 August 2025).

  • Licensing:

  • Cameco Discussions:

Financial & Corporate

Other Projects

  • Quantum Silicon (Q-Si):

  • First production module under construction; target output: 20kg/year of enriched silicon-28.

  • Medical Isotopes (MIST):

  • Prototype testing for ytterbium-176 enrichment (for cancer treatment).

Market Context

  • Uranium term price: ~US$80/lb (near 20-year high).
  • Strong global nuclear demand driven by energy security & AI/data center growth.

Note: Operational timelines remain tentative; commercial outcomes depend on TRL-6 validation, licensing, and funding.

• Key Development: US NRC accepted Global Laser Enrichment’s (GLE) licence application for the Paducah Laser Enrichment Facility (PLEF), advancing regulatory progress for SILEX uranium enrichment technology.
  • Potential Impact: Successful licensing and commercialization could position SILEX as a major contributor to nuclear fuel production (natural uranium, LEU, HALEU) amid strong nuclear industry tailwinds.
  • Risks: Project remains contingent on TRL-6 Pilot success, market conditions, feasibility outcomes, and regulatory approvals.
